articles.title: Americans stranded by Norwegian Cruise save elderly passenger, family says: Ship 'left her to die' - Fox News
articles.description: Julie Lenkoff, 80, suffered a medical emergency on a Norwegian Cruise, which "medically disembarked" her on an African island, but her family said the cruise line never contacted them.
articles.content:
Norwegian Cruise Line forced an 80-year-old woman, who suffered a stroke and possible heart attack, to "medically disembark" on an African island and "left her to die," her family said.
